  "title": "G10 - Operations Support Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Role Overview</strong></p><p>The L1 Support / Webmaster will join a website team supporting the revamp and ongoing operations of a large-scale corporate website. The role focuses on daily website content updates, first-level support, and operational monitoring to ensure stable and compliant website operations.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Perform day-to-day website content updates, including publishing and updating pages, images, and content using a Content Management System (CMS).</li><li>Provide L1 support for website-related issues, including ticket triaging, escalation, and resolution in accordance with defined SLAs.</li><li>Monitor website traffic and performance using web analytics tools and report issues or anomalies where required.</li><li>Maintain and update documentation, knowledge bases, and operational procedures related to website systems and support processes.</li><li>Collaborate with internal stakeholders and vendors to support website revamp initiatives and ongoing enhancements.</li><li>Ensure content accuracy, timeliness, and adherence to operational standards.</li></ul><p><strong>Required Experience & Skills</strong></p><ul><li>Experience in managing and supporting websites on a day-to-day basis.</li><li>Hands-on experience with CMS platforms for publishing and maintaining website content.</li><li>Familiarity with web analytics tools for monitoring traffic and performance.</li><li>Experience using ticketing systems (e.g. JIRA) for issue tracking, escalation, and resolution.</li><li>Understanding of SLA-driven operational support environments.</li><li>Ability to document processes and maintain structured knowledge repositories.</li><li>Strong attention to detail and ability to work independently.</li></ul>",
